[1
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 1998 04:05:56 -0700 (MST)
From: Peter Petrisko <ptp@primenet.com>
Source: The Star, 14 April 1998
At least 10 persons have been admitted to the Beluran district hospital
near Sandakan, while 20 others have been kept in isolation at the
multi-purpose hall in Kota Kinabalu following a cholera outbreak a week
ago.
Among the affected villages were Kampung Simpangun, Kampung Kobuluk and
Kampung Batangan.
