[2
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 1998 09:32:25 -0500
From: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>
Source: The Star Online -April 15

200 Cholera Cases in Sabah
Kota Kinabalu: some 209 cholera cases and another 61 typhoid cases have so
far been reported in Sabah this year as the drought entered its fifth month.
Describing the situation as under control, state medical and health
department deputy director Dr Hasan Abdul Rahman said to date, 913 cholera
cases carriers had been detected in seven districts.
In a statement yesterday, he said the latest cholera cases were reported in
the Labuk Sugut district near Sandakan where 42 people had been infected by
the disease since Saturday.
Another 163 healthy carriers had also been detected in the district.
Semporna had the largest number of people infected with cholera at 96 while
Tawau had the largest number of typhoid cases at 31.
--
Clyde E. Markon, M.D.
Hennepin Faculty Associates
Internal Medicine/Nephrology
Critical Care
e-mail: docmarkon@worldnet.att.net
